Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.44,0:00:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,CHAIN. Critical-component sourcing in a polycrisis world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.44,0:00:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When a Taiwan Strait or Suez disruption hits, which Marine programs\Nare exposed?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.44,0:00:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirty named nodes — TSMC, ASML, rare-earth mines, primes, and USMC\Nend-items.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.44,0:00:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty days of synthetic disruption events stream in — typhoons, cyber,\Nexport controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.45,0:00:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A multi-step LLM agent analyzes the disrupted network — structured\NJSON.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.47,0:00:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a Kamiwaza-deployed model writes a Critical-Component Risk Brief\Nfor PEO Land Systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.48,0:00:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Exposed programs. Substitute suppliers. Lead-time impact. Mitigation\Nplaybook.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.48,0:00:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Three pre-baked scenarios — Taiwan Strait, Suez compound, rare-earth\Nfreeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.99,0:00:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL and the same code runs inside the wire —\Nair-gapped, IL5/IL6 ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.99,0:00:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Powered by the Kamiwaza Stack. Deploy in hours, not months.
